  "content": "The Builder Platform governs creation and extension of the Powerhouse architecture. Instead of building monolithic applications, contributors define document types, schemas, automation rules, and interfaces as reusable modules. These are published to a shared registry where they can be discovered, forked, extended, or monetized. Every time a module is used in another network's deployment, its original authors receive a share of the value generated -- making open-source infrastructure economically sustainable.",
